**Category:** essay-draft practical-knowledge aristotle aquinas nussbaum experimentum prudentia speculative-knowledge

**Abstract:**
Major essay titled "Practical Understanding" continuing 98-APR-1. Extensive analysis of Aristotle-Aquinas on speculative vs. practical knowledge from Metaphysics Lectio 1. Argues there is no speculative knowledge--all knowledge is prospective and practical. Develops distinction between animal experimentum and human knowledge through language. Critiques Nussbaum on "practical necessity." Discusses prudentia in animals vs. humans, deliberation, and contingency of action. Argues "prudentia is the only knowledge there is--not as faithful image but as disposition to respond."

**AI Recommendation:** Major theoretical essay; variant of 98-APR-2. Central to practical knowledge thesis.

